        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 20 at 3:00AM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>A prolonged period of dry weather and dry fuels will result in
elevated fire weather conditions later this morning through
this afternoon across Berkshire County. Although winds will be
rather light from the north to northeast at 5 to 10 mph, the
relative humidity will be lower than Friday. Minimum relative
humidity values will drop to between 25 and 35 percent.

Exercise caution handling any potential ignition sources,
including machinery, cigarettes, and matches. Any fires that
ignite will have potential to spread quickly.

This forecast considers meteorological, fuel, and land conditions
and has been developed in coordination with state fire and land
management officials.
</description>
